Citation.sTitle: Activity coefficients at infinite dilution of organic solutes in the ionic liquid  trihexyltetradecylphosphonium hexafluorophosphate using gas liquid  chromatography at T = (313.15, 333.15, 353.15, and 363.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Activity coefficients at infinite dilution for 31 organic solutes (n-alkanes, alk-1-enes, alk-1-ynes, cycloalkanes, alkylbenzenes, alcohols, and ketones) in the ionic liquid trihexyltetradecylphosphonium hexafluorophosphate [3C6C14P][PF6] were determined by gas-liquid chromatography at T = (313.15,  333.15, 353.15, and 363.15) K. From experimental values, the partial molar excess enthalpy values at infinite dilution, together with the selectivity,  and the capacity (which are related to the separation of liquids) were calculated and compared to literature values for other ionic liquids, as well as industrial solvents.
